Description: Complete seal-impression with two smaller rows of basketry coil impression at the rear and at the side one larger rows, showing that this piece was positioned most likely on the lid of a basket. The fine brown Nile clay shows small inclusions of mica. The top part shows the impression of a small scarab-like seal and quite some finger prints around the seal impression. The seal impression shows a circumferential line and two vertical lines at each end of the seal. In the middle a mn-sign above a horizontal line, above another sign, maybe an Ax.t (N27). The clay was hardened after excavation.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
